Package project_1

Class Collection

java.lang.Object
project_1.Collection
public class Collection
extends java.lang.Object
The class that represents a collection of albums with accompanying methods to update the collection.
Author:
Ethan Chang, Kevin Cubillos

  • Method Details

    • find

      private int find​(Album album)
      Search for an album in the collection using Sequential Search
      Parameters:
      album - target album
      Returns:
      index of target album, NOT_FOUND (-1) otherwise

    • grow

      private void grow()
      Increase the size of the collection by 4 whenever current capacity is reached.

    • add

      public boolean add​(Album album)
      Adds an album if it does not exist in the collection already. The new album is added at the end of the collection. Increase the size of collection if adding album exceeds current capacity.
      Parameters:
      album - the album to be added.
      Returns:
      true if album is added, false if album is already in collection.

    • remove

      public boolean remove​(Album album)
      Deletes an album if it exists in the collection. Shift all albums in collection after deleted album to the left by one.
      Parameters:
      album - the target album
      Returns:
      true if album was deleted, false if album does not exist.

    • lendingOut

      public boolean lendingOut​(Album album)
      Lends out an album, updating availability to not available
      Parameters:
      album - the target album
      Returns:
      true if album was lent out, false if album does not exist.

    • returnAlbum

      public boolean returnAlbum​(Album album)
      Returns an album to the collection, updating availability to is available.
      Parameters:
      album - the target album.
      Returns:
      returns true if album is returned, false if album does not exist.

    • print

      public void print()
      Prints all albums in collection in no particular order.

    • printByReleaseDate

      public void printByReleaseDate()
      Prints all albums in collection in order of release dates. Ordered from oldest to youngest. Uses MergeSort to sort a copy of the collection.

    • printByGenre

      public void printByGenre()
      Prints all albums in collection in order of genre (alphabetically). Uses MergeSort to sort a copy of the collection.

    • mergeSort

      private void mergeSort​(Album[] temp, int l, int r, int order)
      Merge Sort algorithm to sort collections based on order.
      Parameters:
      temp - album collection to be sorted
      l - left index of current sub-array
      r - right index of current sub-array
      order - type of order for sort: 1 for release dates, 2 for genre

    • mergeDate

      private void mergeDate​(Album[] temp, int l, int m, int r)
      Merge Algorithm of MergeSort where release dates are compared.
      Parameters:
      temp - album collection to be sorted
      l - left index of current sub-array
      m - middle index of current sub-array
      r - right index of current sub-array

    • mergeGenre

      private void mergeGenre​(Album[] temp, int l, int m, int r)
      Merge Algorithm of MergeSort where genres are compared.
      Parameters:
      temp - album collection to be sorted
      l - left index of current sub-array
      m - middle index of current sub-array
      r - right index of current sub-array

    • size

      public int size()
      Return the size of the album collection.
      Returns:
